Package edu.brown.cs.student.main

Class Parse<T>

java.lang.Object
edu.brown.cs.student.main.Parse<T>
Type Parameters:
T - A generic type parameter, so that the dataRows object can be generic, according to a strategy pattern.
public class Parse<T> extends Object
Parse class parses a reader object and saves the object as a list of rows, with the row type depending on the CreatorFromRow instance that is used.

  • Method Details

    • parse

      public void parse(Reader reader, CreatorFromRow<T> creatorFromRow, boolean hasHeader)
      Parse method reads in a reader object, converting each row to a list of strings, and then converting each row to whatever the create method returns. The objects returned are added to dataRows which represents the parsed reader object.

    • getDataRows

      public List<T> getDataRows()
      getDataRows() is a simple getter for dataRows.
      Returns:
      dataRows, the object that represents the parsed reader object
